# Critical Assumptions

| Assumption ID | Category              | Assumption                                                                                                                                                                               | Related Requirement / User Story | Risk Level | Current Evidence                                                                                                                | How to Test                                                                                                     |
| ------------- | --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **A-01**      | User Problem          | Students need a faster and more convenient attendance check-in process than manual attendance.                                                                                           | **FR-02, FR-03 / US-01**         | High       | Lab 03 survey and interviews identified slow and inconvenient attendance processes.                                             | Observe students completing the check-in workflow using the clickable prototype and collect feedback.           |
| **A-02**      | Value Proposition     | QR code check-in with GPS verification will reduce proxy attendance and improve attendance accuracy.                                                                                     | **FR-10 / US-02**                | High       | Lab 03 survey found proxy attendance was a common concern among students and lecturers.                                         | Ask users whether the proposed workflow would discourage proxy attendance after using the prototype.            |
| **A-03**      | Usability             | Students can easily understand the QR scanning process, GPS verification, and confirmation messages without assistance.                                                                  | **FR-03, FR-11 / US-03**         | Medium     | No usability testing has been conducted yet.                                                                                    | Conduct a task-based usability test using the clickable prototype.                                              |
| **A-04**      | Technical Feasibility | The clickable web prototype can clearly demonstrate the complete attendance workflow from login to successful check-in, including QR code generation, QR scanning, and GPS verification. | **FR-02 / US-01**                | Medium     | HTML/CSS/JavaScript prototype demonstrates the intended workflow.                                                               | Observe users completing the workflow and identify any navigation or interaction issues.                        |
| **A-05**      | Business Logic        | Lecturers can easily create attendance sessions and understand the attendance information presented on the dashboard.                                                                    | **FR-09, FR-12 / US-05, US-06**  | Medium     | Lecturer interviews highlighted the need to reduce manual attendance management. The prototype displays sample attendance data. | Ask lecturers to generate an attendance session, navigate the dashboard, and explain the information displayed. |
| **A-06**      | Data Handling         | Students can understand their attendance history and attendance percentage from the information displayed.                                                                               | **FR-05, FR-07, FR-08 / US-04**  | Medium     | Prototype uses realistic sample attendance records.                                                                             | Ask students to locate a specific attendance record and interpret their attendance percentage.                  |

